			<description><![CDATA[<p>
If you&rsquo;re interested in joining a company committed to designing cutting edge software solutions for the world&rsquo;s most innovative companies and putting the customer above all else, Zmags is the place for you. The Business Development Manager creates, identifies, and closes sales for Zmags within a specific geographical region. The Business Development Manager must be ambitious self-starter who can create a large pipeline of business within a short period of time. We look for senior sales professionals that have the knowledge and skill set required to close accounts.</p>
<p>
<br />
Expectations:</p>
<p>
&bull; Meet and exceed all established sales objectives.<br />
&bull; Achieve/exceed sales goals through the direct sale of Zmags products and services to enterprises throughout the US.<br />
&bull; Identify and qualify high-value sales opportunities through cold-call prospecting, networking, trade shows, and lead follow up.<br />
&bull; Own the sales cycle &ndash; from lead generation to closure.<br />
&bull; Must be comfortable interfacing with all levels of clients, including CEO/CMO/Vice President of Fortune 1000 companies.<br />
&bull; Conduct thorough discovery, qualify need and strategically prove the value of Zmags solutions to address those needs.<br />
&bull; Actively maintain a sales pipeline in accordance with Zmags process and philosophies.<br />
&bull; Be a team player with a positive attitude and a willingness to contribute to the overall team&rsquo;s success.<br />
&bull; Demonstrated ability to work well in a fast paced, results oriented team environment.</p>
<p>
<br />
Qualified candidates for this position have:</p>
<p>
<br />
&bull; A proven sales hunter and closer.<br />
&bull; 2+ years of experience selling enterprise software solutions.<br />
&bull; Proven success, strategically selling into Fortune 1000 accounts.<br />
&bull; Demonstrated success achieving quota and exceeding expectations on a consistent. basis, as well as a proven history of progressive sales achievement.<br />
&bull; Exceptional in prospecting, qualifying, developing, managing and closing business.<br />
&bull; Proven ability to gain access and develop relationships with senior management.<br />
&bull; Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills.<br />
&bull; Strong organizational and follow-up skills.<br />
&bull; Must have a positive attitude, confident, and desire to be the best.<br />
&bull; Candidates should be experienced in selling software services and comfortable with the SaaS business model.<br />
&bull; BA/BS or equivalent.<br />
&bull; Experience with Salesforce.com a plus.<br />
&bull; Consummate leader &amp; team player &ndash; a &lsquo;sales athlete&rsquo;.</p>
